class Solution {
    public int minimumOneBitOperations(int n) {
        int res = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            res ^= n;
            n >>= 1;
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The pattern of minimum operations follows the Gray-code sequence; the result is the bitwise XOR of all right-shifted copies of n, which collapses to a simple loop.

